==English==

===Etymology===
Named after the astronomer [[w:Gerard_Kuiper|Gerard Kuiper]] (1905-1973); and [[belt]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈkaɪ.pɚ.bɛlt/ <br>
'''Note:''' "Kuiper" is a Dutch surname, and may also be pronounced in the Dutch manner.  However, Gerard Kuiper himself used an American pronunciation.

===Noun===
'''Kuiper belt'''
# A region of [[space]] between 30 and 50 [[Astronomical Unit]]AUs from the sun, roughly confined within a thick band around the [[ecliptic]].  This area is populated by many thousands of [[trans-Neptunian object]]s.

